    Scope and Contents
Kirchner, a veterinarian from Havana, Illinois, recalls his early years and practice: training at McKillips Veterinary College in Chicago, treatment of animal diseases, practicing veterinary medicine in rural areas, and his work to eliminate rabies in Illinois dogs. He also discusses childhood on a Chandlerville farm, in Havana, and anti-German sentiment during WWI. 2 tapes, 180 mins., 33 pp. 
Interview by Cullom Davis, 1978 
OPEN 
See collateral file: interviewer's notes, photographs, photocopies of newspaper clippings, and biographical notes written by Kirchner.  
  
